data.title: Designer's Homes, Dolores Guinness the daughter of Gloria Guinness wears Red Dior, 1959 by Mark Shaw
data.text:
Photographed for Dior, Dolores Guinness was the daughter of Gloria Guinness, the style icon, and the mother of Victoria Niarchos. Garance dress, Spring-Summer 1959 Haute Couture collection, Longue line. All Mark Shaw prints are made to order in limited editions on Hahnemuhle photo rag paper. Each print is Estate stamped on the back and signed and numbered by David Shaw, and accompanied by a letter of authenticity. Lead time is four to six weeks, but we often receive them sooner.

*Please note this image is available in several sizes. Prices increase as editions sell out.

10″ x 15″ image on 11″ x 17″ paper, 13.75″ x 20″ image on 17″ x 22″ paper, 22″ x 32″ image on 24″ x 36″ paper, 32″ x 40″ image on 36″ x 48″ paper, 40″ x 50″ image on 44″ x 54″ paper
